<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Artifacthub on Documentation</title><link>/guides/tutorials/artifacthub/</link><description>Recent content in Artifacthub on Documentation</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="/guides/tutorials/artifacthub/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Publishing Meshery Designs to ArtifactHub</title><link>/guides/tutorials/artifacthub/publish-to-artifacthub/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/guides/tutorials/artifacthub/publish-to-artifacthub/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction"&gt;
	Introduction
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this tutorial, we&amp;rsquo;ll see how to export a Design from Meshery which we will use to populate an ArtifactHub repository.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="prerequisites"&gt;
	Prerequisites
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to the &lt;em&gt;Meshery Playground&lt;/em&gt;. If you don&amp;rsquo;t have an account, sign up at &lt;a href="https://playground.meshery.io/"&gt;Meshery Playground&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="steps"&gt;
	Steps
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-click-on-meshmap"&gt;
	1. Click on MeshMap
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class="content-image" src="../../../guides/tutorials/images/publish-to-artifacthub/2024-07-30_1.png" alt="" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="2-find-the-design-in-the-side-panel"&gt;
	2. Find the Design in the Side Panel
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class="content-image" src="../../../guides/tutorials/images/publish-to-artifacthub/2024-07-30_2.png" alt="" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="3-click-on-export-design"&gt;
	3. Click on Export Design
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class="content-image" src="../../../guides/tutorials/images/publish-to-artifacthub/2024-07-30_3.png" alt="" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>